The Peoples Democratic Party(PDP) has cleared all the 23 local government areas at the just concluded council polls held on Saturday in Benue. The Chairman of Benue State Independent Electoral Commission (BSIEC) Mr Tersoo Loko, disclosed this on Sunday while declaring the results at the commissionâ€™s headquarters in Makurdi. Loko said PDP emerged winner by beating All Progressive Grand Alliance (APGA) and Labour Party (LP) to clench all the council seats in addition to 276 councillorship positions. He thanked his team for a free, fair and credible election stating that this would be the last election he would be conducting as the chairman of BSIEC. He also thanked the people of Benue for their support and was happy that no violence was recorded in any of the polling units. 